      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay i think i get it. so it's like the rebar is basically holding all the tiny bits of the cement matrix together so they don't just fly apart when things get stretched. does the concrete actually \"grip\" the rebar? like is there some kind of bond between the two, or is it just sitting in there? maybe you could explain how that internal interface works to keep everything stable.",
